The Manufacturers Association of Nigeria (MAN)’s Manufacturers Confidence Index (MCCI) was created to gauge the changes in manufacturing activities quarterly as a result of changes in the macroeconomic ambience and Government policies in its released noted that the efficacy of Government’s capital expenditure in spur productivity in the sector  According to the statement excerpts from The Manufacturers Confidence Index  of 400 Chief Executive Officers of MAN member-companies appreciated the efforts of Government to improve the state of infrastructure in the country but opined that the low allocation for provision of infrastructure facility in the yearly budget, the poor implementation of the budgetary provisions and the absence of monitoring and evaluation mechanism to interrogate the implementation of the budget and relevant Executive Orders.  Association further noted that this development has left the country’s infrastructure in a dilapidated state and has not been able to spur the desired economic growth through enhanced real sector productivity.  “The poor performances of the indexes therefore, demand for better management of the macroeconomy; strategic support for the manufacturing sector to maintain production despite the intensity of the second wave of COVID-19; intentional initiatives to better control the spread COVID-19; and the building of institutional framework that will checkmate all forms of restiveness that can dislocate the economy